    {
      "id": 2483,
      "type": "CLIPTextEncode",
      "pos": [
        -4237.010955473756,
        3130.041282732938
      ],
      "size": [
        366.78630349704963,
        219.4493436268085
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 19,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [
        {
          "name": "clip",
          "type": "CLIP",
          "link": 13362
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "CONDITIONING",
          "type": "CONDITIONING",
          "slot_index": 0,
          "links": [
            7065
          ]
        }
      ],
      "title": "CLIP Text Encode (Positive Prompt)",
      "properties": {
        "cnr_id": "comfy-core",
        "ver": "0.3.28",
        "Node name for S&R": "CLIPTextEncode"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Motion focus: Rapid clockwise spin of the chrome pyramid.\n\nBeginning from a near-static hover, the colossal chrome pyramid immediately initiates a fast, smooth clockwise rotation. Within moments it accelerates to a rapid, hypnotic spin—the mirrored facets blur into streaking ribbons of reflected gold, pink, and violet light that spiral across its surface. The spin maintains a consistent high speed throughout, the pyramid's edges cutting through the air, its reflections sweeping across the forest canopy below in rapid, searchlight-like arcs.\n\nSecondary motion: The emerald treetops sway continuously in the wind, leaves rippling in waves. The volumetric sunlight shifts subtly as clouds drift overhead. The pyramid's fast-spinning reflections create dancing highlights that flicker rapidly across the canopy.\n\nCamera movement: Locked off, completely static—no zoom, no pan, no tilt. The stillness of the camera emphasizes the impossible, surreal speed of the spinning megastructure against the gentle natural motion of the forest below.\n\nAudio: Low resonant ambient drone, the shimmering whistle of air displacement from the massive spinning form—a rhythmic whoosh on each rotation. Wind through the distant forest. A deep, subsonic vibration felt more than heard.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#232",
      "bgcolor": "#353"
    },
